    <thetext>Description of problem:
chrony since 3.0 (added in F26) supports HW timestamping on network interfaces. selinux policy doesn&apos;t allow chronyd to enable the timestamping. It doesn&apos;t produce any AVC in logs unless dontaudits are disabled (semodule -DB).

audit: AVC avc:  denied  { net_admin } for  pid=3677 comm=&quot;chronyd&quot; capability=12  scontext=system_u:system_r:chronyd_t:s0 tcontext=system_u:system_r:chronyd_t:s0 tclass=capability permissive=0


Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
selinux-policy-3.13.1-249.fc26.noarch

How reproducible:
always

Steps to Reproduce:
1. find a machine with an interface which supports HW timestamping (e.g. i210, i219, i350, i354)
2. echo &apos;hwtimestamp eth0&apos; &gt;&gt; /etc/chrony.conf
3. systemctl restart chronyd

Actual results:
chronyd[3677]: Fatal error : Could not enable HW timestamping on eth0

Expected results:
HW timestamping enabled

Additional info:</thetext>
